00044 bool parser::parseIns(instruction* newIns) {
00045         //int activeWinRange = iROB->NumElements() - iWinPointer;
00046         newIns->setStatus(fetch, cycle, -1);
00047         while(true) {
00048                 int result = fetchIns(newIns);
00049                 if (result == -1 || (insParseCap > 0 && insParseCap <= insID)) {
00050                         printf("Reached End of File.\n");
00051                         eof = true; //TODO add this line later
00052                         //iROB->RemoveAt(iROB->NumElements()-1);
00053                         delete newIns;
00054                         return false;
00055                 } //EOF
00056                 else if (result == -2) {
00057                         //iROB->RemoveAt(iROB->NumElements()-1);
00058                         //i--;
00059                         continue; //Skip the line and read next line
00060                 } else {
00061                         insID++;
00062                         //printf("insID = %d\n",insID);
00063                         newIns->setInsID(insID);
00064                         newIns->noRRdependencyTable(depTables, coreType);
00065                         //TODO put the block back in when you have the right parameters defined.
00066                         // newIns->br_dependencyTable(depTables);
00067                         // /* Manage LSQ */ 
00068                         // if (memoryModel == PERFECT) {
00069                         //      newIns->perfetc_MemDependencyTable(depTables, coreType, numSideBuffs);
00070                         // } else if (memoryModel == TOTAL_ORDER) {
00071                         //      newIns->totalOrder_MemDependencyTable(totalOrderLSQ);
00072                         // }
00073                         /*-----STAT-----*/
00074                         //numParentsHist->addElem(newIns->getNumAncestors());
00075                         /*-----STAT-----*/
00076                         if (reschedule == false && makePhrase == false)
00077                                 iWindow->Append(newIns);
00078                         iROB->Append(newIns);
00079                         newIns->findPhraseAncestors(); //TODO this should go somewhere else
00080                         //printf("TEST: newIndx = %d, ROB size = %d\n", *iWindow->Nth(iWindow->NumElements()-1), iROB->NumElements());
00081                         break;
00082                 }
00083         }
00084         return true;
00085 }

00366 long int parser::getReg(char *c) {
00367         int i = 0, start = 0, end = 0;
00368         char temp[INS_STRING_SIZE];
00369 
00370         //Parse a x86 resgiter name
00371         while (c[i]=='z') {i++;}
00372         if (c[i] == ',') {
00373                 resetInput(c,i);
00374                 i++;
00375                 start = i;
00376                 while (c[i] != '#' && c[i] != '\0' && c[i] != '\n') {
00377                         temp[i] = c[i];
00378                         resetInput(c,i);
00379                         if (debug) printf("temp[i] = %c\n", temp[i]);
00380                         if (c[i] == ',') return -1; //corrupt ins
00381                         i++;
00382                 }
00383                 end = i;
00384                 if (c[i] == '\n' || c[i] == '\0') return -3; //End of line
00385         }
00386         int size = end - start;
00387         char * reg = new char[size+1];
00388         for (i=0; i < size; i++) {
00389                 reg[i] = temp[i+start];
00390                 if (debug) printf("reg [i] = %c, size = %d", reg[i], size);
00391         }
00392         reg[size] = '\0';
00393         //for (i=0; i < (end-start); i++) {
00394         //      if (debug) printf("%c", reg[i], size);
00395         //}
00396         long int result =  RF->getRegNum(reg);
00397         delete [] reg;

00433 long int parser::getANumber(char *c) {
00434         int i = 0, start = 0, end = 0;
00435         char temp[INS_STRING_SIZE];
00436 
00437         //Parse a x86 resgiter name
00438         while (c[i]=='z') {i++;}
00439         if (c[i] == ',' || c[i] == ' ') {
00440                 resetInput(c,i);
00441                 i++;
00442                 start = i;
00443                 while (c[i] != ',' && c[i] != '\0' && c[i] != '\n' && c[i] != ')') {
00444                         temp[i] = c[i];
00445                         resetInput(c,i);
00446                         if (debug) printf("temp[i] = %c\n", temp[i]);
00447                         i++;
00448                 }
00449                 //if (c[i] == '\n' || c[i] == '\0') return -3; //End of line (unsigned return)
00450                 end = i;
00451         }
00452         int size = end - start;
00453         char * addr = new char[size];
00454         for (i=0; i < (end-start); i++) {
00455                 addr[i] = temp[i+start];
00456                 if (addr[i] < 48 || addr[i] > 57) return 0; //corrupt number
00457                 if (debug) printf("addr [i] = %c, size = %d\n", addr[i], size);
00458         }
00459         long int result = 0;
00460         for (i = size-1; i >= 0; i--) {
00461                 long int tenPow = 1;
00462                 for (int j = 0; j < size-1-i; j++) {
00463                         tenPow *= 10;}
00464                 result += ((long int)addr[i]-48)*tenPow;
00465         }
00466         if (debug) printf("ins addr = %s, result = %ld\n", addr, result);
00467         //No negative or zero values allowed
00468         if (result <= 0) {
00469                 delete [] addr;
00470                 return 0; //corrupt number
00471         }
00472         delete [] addr;
00473         return result;
00474 }
